attribute(name) actually gets normalised to attribute(name,xsd:anySimpleType);
this checks that when it's printed out the simpler equivalent is used, even
when anySimpleType was explicitly specified

=================================== PROGRAM ====================================
testxpath
==================================== INPUT =====================================
$test instance of attribute(xsd:foo,xsd:anySimpleType)
==================================== OUTPUT ====================================
$test instance of attribute(xsd:foo)
================================== RETURN CODE =================================
0
